vulnerability.name: USN-7223-1
vulnerability.description: Frank Zeng discovered that OpenJPEG incorrectly handled memory when using the decompression utility. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service or execute arbitrary code. (CVE-2024-56826, CVE-2024-56827)

statements.status_notes: OpenJPEG could be made to crash or run programs if it opened a specially crafted file.
